<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-06-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-06-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="698" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d698">
                        <head>No. 696.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Preston</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Hayti</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-06-24"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 24,
                                1888</date>.<lb/>(Received June 25.)</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of State</hi>: I have the honor to
                            announce to you that Messrs. C. A. de Chambrun, George S. Boutwell, and
                            James G. Berret are the counsel for the Haytian Government in the case
                            of C. A. Van Bokkelen, which is submitted to Mr. Alexander P. Morse as
                            arbitrator.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Stephen
                                    Preston.</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>